This paper deals with the security of Internet routing protocols, specifically BGP and S-BGP, which are used for exchanging routing information between Autonomous Systems (ASes). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses the computational complexity of traffic hijacking, which falls under the category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Additionally, the paper involves the study of algorithms and optimization problems, which could be categorized under cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity). Finally, the paper deals with the analysis of network protocols, which could be classified under cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing).
